The same remark applies to this ode as to many others, that those who believe it to have reference to real persons, and the jealousy to be any thing but 0 poetical jealousy, have mistaken the character of Horace's writings. It would be difficult to imagine the man who wrote these verses really jealous while he was writing them, or much acquainted with that passion.
